verses.roman:
avaśya caliba, duṅhe karaha sammati
tomā-duṅhā vinā mora nāhi anya gati

synonyms: avaśya—certainly; caliba—I shall go; duṅhe—both of you; karaha sammati—kindly agree to this proposal; tomā-duṅhā vinā—except you two; mora—My; nāhi—there is not; anya gati—other resort.
translation: "This time I must go. Will you please give Me permission? Save for you two, I have no other resort.
